Package: cognitive-grip
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, libcogutil-dev, opencog-atomspace, atomspace-storage
Description: Cognitive-Grip: Unified Abstraction Layer for AGI-OS
 Cognitive-Grip provides seamless integration between CogNumach, HurdCog,
 and OpenCog components. It serves as the central coordination point for
 cognitive synergy across all layers of the AGI Operating System.
 .
 Key features:
  - Unified AtomSpace access
  - Microkernel interface abstraction
  - Operating system service integration
  - Cognitive component registration and invocation
  - Storage backend coordination
  - Knowledge graph persistence
 .
 This package is essential for AGI-OS integration and must be installed
 after atomspace-storage and before higher-level cognitive components.

Package: cognitive-grip-dev
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, cognitive-grip (= ${binary:Version}), libcogutil-dev, opencog-atomspace
Description: Development files for Cognitive-Grip
 This package contains the header files and development libraries for
 building applications and components that use the Cognitive-Grip API.
 .
 Install this package if you need to develop cognitive components for
 the AGI-OS framework.
